placeable natural heritage, and also would devastate our national parks, forests, and other public lands.   To safeguard wildlife and their habitats, it is essential to consolidate protected areas and prioritize natural systems over mining, grazing, drilling, and logging. Grand Canyon For Sale provides an excellent overview of the physical and biological challenges facing public lands. The book also exposes and shows how to combat the political activity that threatens these places in the U.S. today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Jan 2020) 0aPublic landsxEnvironmental aspectsxUnited States. 4aamerican culture. 4abackpackers. 4aconsumerism. 4aeconomist. 4aenvironmentalism. 4aforeclosure. 4aforests. 4ahikers. 4anational parks. 4anatural history. 4anorth america. 4aon the ground reporting. 4aphysical and biological challenges. 4apreservation. 4apreservationists. 4apublic land. 4apublic lands. 7aSCIENCE / Natural History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520965249423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/doc/cover/9780520965249.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles